description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen within the Emergency Surgery and Elective Care Business Unit on Ward 3 Hexham General Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward 3 is a 24 bedded ward which consists of 17 orthopaedic beds for elective procedures following the fast track protocol and a 7 bedded surgical pod in which we provide care for pre and post-operative patients undergoing a range of surgical procedures including gynecology, plastics, urology, dental and general surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a well motivated enthusiastic individual to join our team on ward 3. Our ward strives to deliver high quality, holistic care to all of our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We encourage our staff to develop their skills through a variety of learning opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to provide high standards of care and should also demonstrate excellent communication skills and a flexible approach.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Criteria;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;. Understanding of patient basic needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;. Previous care experience preferably in a healthcare setting&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;.Must be flexible to meet the needs of the service and be able to work a variety of shifts including days and nights.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date- 16th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDenise ArmstrongJob titleWard ManagerEmail addressdenise.armstrong@nhct.nhs.ukTelephone number01434655475&lt;/p&gt;
